'''Romano Christian Schmid''' (born 27 January 2000) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref name="sw">{{cite web |title=R. Schmid |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/romano-schmid/438002/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=24 December 2020}}</ref>

==Club career==
In January 2019, Schmid joined [[Bundesliga]] side [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Werder holt Schmid und verleiht ihn gleich weiter|url=https://www.kicker.de/werder-holt-schmid---und-verleiht-ihn-gleich-weiter-739237/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|date=3 January 2019|language=de}}</ref> The same year on 5 February, he was sent on loan to [[Wolfsberger AC]] for the rest of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Romano Schmid unterschreibt|url=https://www.rzpelletswac.at/2019/02/05/romano-schmid-unterschreibt/|website=RZ Pellets WAC|date=5 February 2019|access-date=2 April 2022|language=de}}</ref> In April 2022, he agreed a contract extension with Werder Bremen.<ref>{{cite web |title=Romano Schmid verlängert in Bremen|url=https://www.kicker.de/ein-ausschlaggebender-grund-schmid-verlaengert-vorzeitig-in-bremen-896580/artikel|website=Kicker|access-date=2 April 2022|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
On 22 September 2022, Schmid debuted for the [[Austria national football team|Austrian senior squad]] in a 2–0 loss against [[France national football team|France]] at the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Christian|last=Hackl|title=Österreich verliert in Frankreich 0–2 und spielt nun gegen den Abstieg|url=https://www.derstandard.at/story/2000139339702/oesterreich-verliert-in-frankreich-02|website=[[Der Standard]]|date=22 September 2022|language=de}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Nationalteam-Kader für UEFA EURO 2024 fixiert |trans-title=Final national team squad for UEFA EURO 2024 |url=https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/OeFB-Kader-UEFA-EURO-2024 |language=de |publisher=[[Austrian Football Association]] |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> On 25 June, he scored his first international goal in a 3–2 victory over the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] during the final group stage match of the European competition, helping his country secure the [[UEFA Euro 2024 Group D|top spot in their group]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Ames |first=Nick |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/jun/25/netherlands-austria-euro-2024-match-report |title=Austria top group with Netherlands in third after Sabitzer strike settles thriller |work=The Guardian |date=25 June 2024 }}</ref>

